      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those symptoms are common early on as your body acclimates to lithium, but they can also indicate toxicity if your dosage is too high. Since you started recently, you should check if your blood levels are within the therapeutic range and keep taking your current dose as prescribed. If you feel severe vomiting, confusion, or excessive tremors, contact your prescriber immediately before adjusting anything yourself.",
