      "content": "No, you should absolutely not increase your lithium dose on your own, as this drastically increases the risk of severe toxicity and permanent damage. The lightheadedness and cramping are warning signs that your body is struggling with the current levels, so you need to contact your doctor immediately for guidance rather than trying to push through it. Missing doses is dangerous for your mood, but taking too much lithium is a medical emergency that requires professional intervention right away.",
